data.name: catapult
data.description: automated mass spec data search and analysis tool

evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "3. Download the repository to your local machine."

"Catapult is an automated tool for running Mass Spectrometry Search on files generated by the instrument. It is used to watch for new files and process them as they are created according to specified experimental parameters."

Installation instructions: "3. Download the repository to your local machine. 4. Open a terminal and navigate to the repository. 5. Run `pip install -r requirements.txt` ... 6. Run `docker-compose up -d` to start the application. 7. Open a web browser and navigate to `http://localhost/admin` to access the application."
